I think there is a bug in below code. 
{code}
try {
  nmContext.getNMStateStore().storeAssignedResources(containerId,
    RESOURCE_TYPE, allocatedDevices);
} catch (IOException e) {
    throw new ResourceHandlerException(e);
}
{code}

When storeAssignedResources failed, there will be a leak. Because postComplete will never be called. It means usedDevices won't be removed. So should add cleanupAssignGpus in catch section.

